        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-23T14:02:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not trying to do anything novel here; I\u0027m just repeating the logic from RunInSeries, but simplified to only support the 2-item case. (RunInSeries supports replacing an arbitrary number of leading nodes, which just requires more logic.)\n\nHonestly I have not spent much time at all on analysis; this is definitely not a first step towards any bigger analysis redesign.\n\nTBH I think the analysis pass is probably not very worthwhile right now, as it doesn\u0027t seem to do any analysis of child subtrees. It assumes that we have a sequential array of simple processors, which used to be the common case, but now we will most often have a complex tree starting from a single node. It probably needs to be redesigned from scratch to descend the tree and see if any subtrees can be replaced with const-color. Right now it doesn\u0027t descend the trees at all.",
